Hi Patrick, 

IBM team had a concern about making a POWER10 specific inventory item (the first time we are doing this in inventory) 

The suggestion is, can we use like below for guard requirement to show the guarded unit name to the external user. 

```
- /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.Cpu
 - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0/core0 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.CpuCore + PrettyName as Core
 - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0/coreN - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.CpuCore + PrettyName as Core
 - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0/unit1 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item + PrettyName as Memory controller (any preferable name)
 - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0/unit2 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item + PrettyName as OMIC (any preferable name)
...
- /system/chassis/motherrboard/dimm0 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.Dimm + PrettyName as Memory (any preferable name)
```

Patch Set 6:

> IBM team had a concern about making a POWER10 specific inventory item (the first time we are doing this in inventory) 

What is the concern?

> ```
> - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.Cpu
>  - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0/core0 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.CpuCore + PrettyName as Core
>  - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0/coreN - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.CpuCore + PrettyName as Core
>  - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0/unit1 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item + PrettyName as Memory controller (any preferable name)
>  - /system/chassis/motherrboard/proc0/unit2 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item + PrettyName as OMIC (any preferable name)
> ...
> - /system/chassis/motherrboard/dimm0 - xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.Dimm + PrettyName as Memory (any preferable name)
> ```

PrettyName is intended to be displayed in user interfaces.  So, dimm0 might be something like "DIMM-A1" because that is the silkscreen identifier and used throughout the server manual (your systems may use an entirely different identifier scheme here, so take that as an example).  PrettyName should not be used in any programmatic way, which is what you're proposing here.
